": "Arvutisüsteemid ja arvutisüsteemide haldamisega seotud mõisted, süsteemihalduse baasressursid: salvestid, arvutusjõudlus, ribalaius, tarkvara, ressursside virtualiseerimine; protsessid süsteemihalduses: arvutisüsteemide planeerimine, arendamine, testimine, juurutamine, hooldus. Dokumenteerimine, seire, kasutajatugi, probleemilahendus, riskihaldus arvutisüsteemide haldamise seisukohalt. Praktikumides tehakse läbi süsteemi põhilised eluetapid Linux operatsioonisüsteemi näitel."}, "objectives": [{"en": "The goal of this course is to give students basic knowledge about Linux based system administration.", "et": "Kursuse eesmärgiks on anda kuulajatele alusteadmised Linuxi põhiste arvutisüsteemide haldamisest."}], "learning_outcomes": [{"en": "After this course students will have basic knowledge on the following topics:", "et": "Tudengid omandavad  põhiteadmised järgmistel aladel: "}, {"en": "base resources of computer systems - storage, computing power, bandwidth, software, resource virtualization; best practices in system administration; processes in system administration - planning, risk management, implementation, testing, maintenance, monitoring, documenting, service support, problem management;", "et": "arvutisüsteemide alusressurssid - salvestid, arvutusjõudlus, ribalaius, tarkvara; ressursside virtualiseerimine; süsteemihalduse parimad praktikad; protsessid süsteemihalduses - planeerimine, riskihaldus, juurutamine, testimine, hooldus, seire, dokumenteerimine, teenuste tugi, probleemilahendus;"}, {"en": "Acquired skills include:", "et": "Omandatavad oskused hõlmavad:"}, {"en": "planning systems and services; implementing services; service monitoring; service maintenance; problem management in computer systems;", "et": "süsteemide ja teenuste planeerimine; teenuste juurutamine; teenuste seire; süsteemide hooldus;  probleemilahendus arvutisüsteemides;"}], "notes": {"et": "See the course web page on https://courses.cs.ut.ee/2025/sa/spring"}}, "grading": {"independent_work": {"et": "For lab instructions see the course web page on https://courses.cs.ut.ee/2025/sa/spring\nTopics covered:\n1. Overview of the linux system (Linux Boot process, Linux kernel, Linux environment)\n2. CentOS\n3. Creating virtual hard drive, preparing OS, private cloud deployment, accessing OS over cloud management interface\n4. Network Configuration, SSH, DNS, Mail server, Apache, File server ... and more if we have extra time\n3. Security: securing services, private/public keys, certificates, authorities, firewall, NAT\n4. Tracking and monitoring (form low level routines: top, htop, nmap, tcpdump, netstat, iostat ... to higher level.\n5. Automation and orchestration (Ansible, Docker, Kubernetes...)"}, "independent_work_assessments": [{"work_type": {"code": "practical", "et": "Praktiline ülesanne", "en": "practical assignment"}, "description": {"et": "All labs must be completed 100% to be allowed to attend final exam"}}], "grade_preconditions": {"et": "1. All labs must be completed ( all the lab tests should be OK  to be eligible for the final exam).\n2. For passing the course student should get at least 51% in total (50% from practical labs work and 1% from practical exam)"}, "grade_evaluation": {"et": "Labs give 50% of the final grade \nAll Lab tasks have to be completed 100% in order to be allowed to take the examination.\nExam gives 50% of the final grade"}, "debt_elimination": {"et": "In agreement with the lecturer"}, "assessment_scale": {"code": "grade", "et": "Eristav (A, B, C, D, E, F, mi)", "en": "differentiated (A, B, C, D, E, F, not present)"}, "results_available_from": {}}, "resources": {"web_based": {"code": "2", "et": "põimõpe", "en": "blended learning"}, "website_url": "https://courses.cs.ut.ee/2025/sa/spring", "is_moodle_connected": false}, "participants": {"lecturers": [{"person_uuid": "70f8d045-6d2b-98be-1290-779ab1425c4f", "person_name": "Rasmus Soome", "structural_unit": {"code": "LTAT07", "name": {"en": "High Performance Computing 